  { '@type': 'Question', name: 'Are post-workout gummies worth it for casual exercisers?', acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'For casual exercisers (2-3 moderate sessions per week), basic post-workout nutrition (a balanced meal with protein and carbohydrates within 2 hours) is usually sufficient for recovery. Post-workout gummies provide the most benefit for: (1) Athletes training 5-7 days per week who need accelerated recovery between sessions. (2) Individuals experiencing significant delayed-onset muscle soreness (DOMS). (3) Older adults (40+) whose natural recovery capacity is declining. (4) Athletes in competition phases with multiple events in short timeframes. If you are training moderately and recovering well with regular nutrition, post-workout gummies are a convenience but not a necessity. If you are pushing training volume and struggling with soreness or recovery, they provide measurable benefit.' } },
