      <p><strong>Post-workout gummies do not replace adequate protein intake.</strong> Muscle protein synthesis requires 20-40g of complete protein (containing all essential amino acids, especially leucine). Gummies cannot deliver this protein quantity. Use post-workout gummies alongside a protein source (shake, whole food, or protein gummies) — not as a protein substitute. For athletes training at high volume, total daily protein of 1.6-2.2g per kg body weight remains the primary driver of recovery and adaptation.</p>
