    <div class="tested-box"><h3>How We Tested These Post-Workout Gummies</h3><ol><li><strong>Purchased independently.</strong> All 14 products were purchased at full retail price from Amazon and sports nutrition retailers.</li><li><strong>Verified active ingredient doses.</strong> Independent laboratory analysis confirmed tart cherry anthocyanin content, BCAA amounts, electrolyte mineral levels, and collagen peptide doses matched label claims.</li><li><strong>8-week recovery assessment.</strong> Sixteen trained athletes incorporated each product into their post-workout routine during structured 8-week training blocks, tracking DOMS severity (VAS scale), next-day performance readiness, and inflammation markers (CRP, IL-6).</li><li><strong>Soreness measurement protocol.</strong> Visual analog scale (VAS) soreness ratings were collected at 24, 48, and 72 hours post-exercise across standardized eccentric-heavy leg training sessions.</li><li><strong>Electrolyte rehydration assessment.</strong> Post-exercise body weight changes and urine specific gravity measurements evaluated rehydration effectiveness of electrolyte-containing products.</li><li><strong>Taste and compliance tracking.</strong> Daily compliance rates were monitored to assess whether taste and convenience drove consistent use — the primary determinant of real-world effectiveness.</li></ol></div>

