    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions About Post-Workout Gummies</h2>
    <details class="fq"><summary>What should post-workout gummies contain?</summary><p>Best ingredients: tart cherry (anti-inflammatory, reduces DOMS by 13%), BCAAs (muscle protein synthesis via mTOR), electrolytes (rehydration), collagen (connective tissue), turmeric (COX-2 inhibition), glutamine (gut barrier + immune). Look for 2-3 at clinical doses.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>When should I take post-workout gummies?</summary><p>Within 30-60 minutes after training for optimal benefit. Anti-inflammatory compounds are most effective before inflammatory markers peak (2-4 hours post-exercise). The protein synthesis window is wider (24-48 hours), but consistent timing builds daily compliance.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Do post-workout gummies replace protein shakes?</summary><p>No. Gummies complement shakes. Protein synthesis requires 20-40g complete protein that gummies cannot deliver. Gummies excel at concentrated bioactives (tart cherry, curcumin, collagen) that shakes do not contain. Use both for comprehensive recovery.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Are post-workout gummies worth it for casual exercisers?</summary><p>Most beneficial for athletes training 5-7 days/week, those with significant DOMS, adults 40+ with slower recovery, and athletes in competition phases. Casual exercisers (2-3 sessions/week) may recover adequately with balanced post-workout meals.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Can I take post-workout gummies on rest days?</summary><p>Yes. Continue tart cherry and collagen on rest days (recovery occurs during rest). Reduce electrolyte and BCAA supplementation on rest days unless protein intake is low. Rest-day recovery supplementation supports the ongoing repair process.</p></details>

